    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2003 BMW M3 featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power plant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS system to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The chassis has been properly addressed with rear subframe reinforcement and refreshed bushings, mitigating common E46-generation fatigue. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec variable M differential lock. The suspension is fitted with Bilstein dampers to maintain strict geometry during high-lateral load cornering. While the vehicle shows minor aesthetic patina consistent with a well-loved driver's car, the drivetrain and cooling system are in robust health, offering the visceral, analog feedback enthusiasts demand.",
